17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 7-602, as
19 amended by Section 88, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 7-602), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 7-602. A. 1. The owner of a motor vehicle registered
22 in this state shall carry in the vehicle at all times a current
23 owner's security verification form listing the vehicle or an
24 equivalent form which has been issued by the Department of Public
HB2980 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Safe ty, and the operator of the vehicle shall produce the form upon
2 request for inspection by any law enforcement officer or
3 representative of the Department and, in case of an accident, the
4 form shall be shown upon request to any person affected by the
5 accident.
6 2. a. Every person registering a motor vehicle in this
7 state, except a motor vehicle which is not being used
8 upon the public highways or public streets, or a
9 manufactured home while on a permanent foundation, at
10 the time of registration of the vehicle, shall certify
11 the existence of security with respect to the vehicle
12 by providing to a licensed operator or other
13 registering agency necessary information from the
14 current owner's security verification in a manner that
15 allows verification of coverage through the online
16 verification system. The information shall include
17 the name or number issued by the National Association
18 of Insurance Commissioners of the current insurance
19 carrier authorized to do business in this state and
20 the policy number applicable to the vehicle being
21 registered. A licensed operator or other registering
22 agency shall require the submission of the form or
23 other verifying information prior to processing an
24 application for registration or renewal.
HB2980 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 b. Every licensed operator or other registering agency
2 shall use the online verification system to certify
3 the existence of security with respect to the vehicle
4 from an insurance carrier authorized to do business in
5 this state unless the online verification system is
6 not online or the required information is otherwise
7 not available, or the licensed operator determines, in
8 the exercise of reasonable discretion, that a physical
9 proof of insurance presented by the customer appears
10 valid and sufficient to demonstrate the existence of
11 the required security. In such a case, the licensed
12 operator or other registering agency may accept
13 verification as provided in subparagraph a of this
14 paragraph, a physical proof of insurance presented by
15 the customer, or from a licensed insurance producer or
16 customer service representative to certify the
17 existence of the required insurance prior to
18 processing any application for motor vehicle
19 registration. Every licensed operator or other
20 registering agent shall allow submission of proof from
21 a licensed insurance producer or customer service
22 representative pursuant to this subparagraph via
23 electronic mail at no additional cost to the person
24 registering the vehicle.
HB2980 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 3. Fleet vehicles operating under the authority of the
2 Corporation Commission, the Federal Highway Administration, or
3 vehicles registered pursuant to the provisions of Section 1120 of
4 this title, shall certify the existence of security with respect to
5 each vehicle at the time of registration by submitting one of the
6 following:
7 a. a current owner's security verification form verifying
8 the existence of security as required by the
9 Compulsory Insurance Law, or
10 b. a permit number verified by the Corporation Commission
11 indicating the existence of a current liability
12 insurance policy. Provided, in the event the
13 Corporation Commission is unable to verify the
14 existence of insurance as provided herein in a prompt
15 and timely fashion, the Corporation Commission may
16 accept a current single state registration form issued
17 by the Corporation Commission or any other regulating
18 entity with which the Corporation Commission has
19 entered into a reciprocal compact or agreement
20 regarding the regulation of motor vehicles engaged in
21 interstate or foreign commerce upon and over the
22 public highways.
23 4. The following shall not be required to carry an owner's or
24 operator's security verification form or an equivalent form from the
HB2980 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 Depa rtment of Public Safety during operation of the vehicle and
2 shall not be required to surrender a security verification form for
3 vehicle registration purposes:
4 a. any vehicle owned or leased by the federal or state
5 government, or any agency or political subdivision
6 thereof,
7 b. any vehicle bearing the name, symbol, or logo of a
8 business, corporation or utility on the exterior and
9 which is in compliance with the provisions of the
10 Compulsory Insurance Law according to records of the
11 Corporation Commission which reflect a deposit or
12 fleet policy,
13 c. fleet vehicles maintaining current vehicle liability
14 insurance as required by the Corporation Commission or
15 any other regulating entity,
16 d. any licensed taxicab, and
17 e. any vehicle owned by a licensed used motor vehicle
18 dealer.
19 5. Any person who knowingly issues or promulgates false or
20 fraudulent information in connection with either an owner's or
21 operator's security verification form or an equivalent form which
22 has been issued by the Department of Public Safety shall be guilty
23 of a misdemeanor and upon conviction shall be subject to a fine not
24
HB2980 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 exce eding Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00), or imprisonment for not
2 more than six (6) months, or by both such fine and imprisonment.
3 B. Each licensed operator is authorized to charge a fee of One
4 Dollar and fifty cents ($1.50) to each person to whom the licensed
5 operator issues a certificate of registration and who is required to
6 surrender proof of financial responsibility, or for whom the
7 licensed operator certifies the existence of financial
8 responsibility through an authorized online certification system,
9 pursuant to the provisions of the Compulsory Insurance Law. The fee
10 may be retained by the licensed operator as compensation for
11 services in processing the proof of financial responsibility and for
12 processing the driver license information, insurance verification
13 information, and other additional information furnished to the
14 licensed operator pursuant to Section 1112 of this title, if such
15 licensed operator does not receive the maximum compensation as
16 authorized by law.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
